President Muhammadu Buhari on Thursday met behind closed doors with former President Goodluck Jonathan at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. The former president, who arrived around 1:45 pm, left at 2:01pm after 15 minutes talks with President Buhari. The agenda of his meeting with the president was not known. This is the sixth time the former president would be visiting the Presidential Villa after losing his re-election bid in 2015. He was last seen in the State House on October 10, 2019. Ex-President Jonathan keeps mum after meeting Buhari at Aso Rock Jonathan visits Buhari at Aso Rock UPDATED: Buhari, Jonathan in 5-minute meeting